snippet.textDisplay:
Reminds me of that scene in 'Howard Stern's Private Parts' where the execs are discussing a listeners survey about Howard's NBC Radio show.
One of them says "Everybody that loves him wants to keep on listening."
"Why?" Says the other.
"Because they want to hear what he's gonna say next. Even people that hate him want to keep on listening!"
"What? Why?!"
"Because they want to hear what he's gonna say next!"

It was pretty much a Howard Stern kind of vibe going on - and I think that was deliberate! Who the hell would be talking about the Golden Globes a week after, at least, if it had been presented by, I dunno Tim Allen? Just look at the attention NBC got, and look at how much continuous ad revenue clicks it would have generated!

Fuck it! I want Dave Chappelle to host the Oscars!

snippet.textDisplay:
This is what's so basic and shortsighted about Rogan and his ilk. Too unnuanced and lazy to just say celebrities/musicians/athletes are virtue signaling when they speak their truth to power. It makes absolute sense for anyone with a huge platform to use it to underscore whatever cause they want. It's actually the perfect time given millions of people are watching. At the end of the day who really gives a shit about hearing about an award for acting/ or watching a football game, when real life shit is affecting people. In other words, when you have the mic, use it, whether we want to hear your bullshit or not. It's disingenuous of you not to, given the huge platform you're afforded, that most people aren't.

B) Funny how Rogan doesn't dare call out a Gervais for his own virtue signaling. I could very well argue that Gervais was out to virtue signal to his narrow minded/ basic taste in comedy folk. You know, that segment of people who seemingly get off when comedians get on a high horse, feeling themselves for refusing to be politically correct. When I saw Gervais's tired shitick, that's exactly what I thought. Just another fool who wants to metaphorically pound his chest and think he's edgy because for not conforming to the times. Lame and definitely not funny.
